    • Method Detail

      • setMaxDays

        public PolicyTypes.Info.Builder setMaxDays(java.lang.Long maxDays)
        Maximum number of days a password may be used. If the password is older than this, a password change will be forced. This property was added in vSphere API 6.7. If null then the restriction will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        maxDays - New value for the property.

      • setMinDays

        public PolicyTypes.Info.Builder setMinDays(java.lang.Long minDays)
        Minimum number of days allowed between password changes. Any password changes attempted sooner than this will be rejected. This property was added in vSphere API 6.7. If null then the restriction will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        minDays - New value for the property.

      • setWarnDays

        public PolicyTypes.Info.Builder setWarnDays(java.lang.Long warnDays)
        Number of days warning given before a password expires. A zero means warning is given only upon the day of expiration. This property was added in vSphere API 6.7. If null then no warning will be provided.
        Parameters:
        warnDays - New value for the property.
